    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the \"beauty of the mundane\" feels like a lie i tell myself to keep going. but i don't want to keep going. if everything just ends in entropy anyway, why am i fighting so hard to stay in this cycle of just existing? it feels like i'm just delaying the inevitable.",
